reviews.review: chock full of political correctness and written to the level of 6th graders

The movie was epic, huge battle scenes, evil Dark side villains, torment, anguish, redemption. Was there some forced contrived dialogue? Yep. Were there some plot moments you went "huh?" Did we go places that had you scratching your head? Absolutely. But as in GOT, you try to wrap up a cultural phenomenon; you try to tie up every loose end and do something brilliant and unique that satisfies the throngs. A tall task. Please take note of the AUDIENCE rating for this film, not the critics, most of who weren't even alive when StarWars began. I enjoyed the film; it paid homage to many of the characters and tropes we've grown to love over the years. Does it feel like something we've seen before? Of course it does, as it should. So, out on your vintage Star Wars t-shirt and grab a bucket of 29.95 popcorn and sit back and enjoy. Damn the critics. Light sabers and Ewoks ahead.

It was essentially a re-hash of the older series.  Rebels have the odds stacked against them, comes down to 1 person who is conflicted but then comes back to their senses.  Main characters are killed off.  Same story of the "Skywalker" saga since the first Star Wars release.  Although good ending of an era hopefully the story continues with other characters and spin offs.
Classic end to the Star Wars saga.  Loved how they tied together elements from episodes 4-6 and some of the "special appearances"!
Soooooo much better than the Last Jedi. There were only a couple of outrageous new in heard of force things posited in the film. Good ending to the story.
Much better than the last Jedi.
The movie was awesome!!!  Loved every minute of it!!!
nothing is ever perfect, but this movie was a fun ride and a welcome addition. Bravo JJ!

The writing and editing was bad. Used a quickly redone script to address Carrie Fishers death by filling with rehashed story ideas. Battles are over the top with franchise characters doing what they always do.
